The paper deals with the security of drone delivery systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also formulates a game-theoretic model to analyze the security of the system, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also deals with the optimization of the delivery time, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also incorporates prospect theory, which is a behavioral economics concept, into the game-theoretic model, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the path selection of the drones, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO).
